<L>__{interior walter's apartment building later}
<A>__{walter is walking up the stairs carrying a briefcase. he passes a middle aged man who is walking down the stairs with a small dog on a leash.}
<P>__{middle aged man (o.s.)}
<D>__{excuse me.}
<A>__{walter stops and turns.}
<C>__{walter}
<D>__{yes. middle aged man are you mr. vale?}
<C>__{walter}
<D>__{yes. middle aged man i thought so. how are you? it's me, jacob konigsberg. do you remember me?}
<A>__{walter doesn't.}
<C>__{jacob}
<D>__{i used to live here with my mother. your wife used to give me piano lessons.}
<C>__{walter}
<D>__{oh. right.}
<C>__{jacob}
<D>__{it has been a long time. i thought that maybe you sold the place. oh. this is sprinkles.}
<P>__{(to the dog)}
<D>__{say "hi", sprinkles. is your wife here with you?}
<C>__{walter}
<D>__{no. she passed away.}
<C>__{jacob}
<D>__{what?! no! i had no idea. i'm so sorry. she was such a nice lady. and i just loved listening to her play.}
<C>__{walter}
<D>__{how's your mother?}
<C>__{jacob}
<D>__{she moved to florida. now i live here. it's nice. there are a lot of new faces. i hardly know anyone anymore. but i have sprinkles so...}
<C>__{walter}
<D>__{nice to see you, jacob.}
<C>__{jacob}
<D>__{you too, mr. vale. goodbye. welcome back.}
<A>__{walter nods and keeps walking.}
